Banks Should Hold 20% Capital, Bank of England’s Miles Says

-- B y   B e n   M o s h i n s k y
-- 
2011-10-04T09:31:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/banks-should-hold-20-capital-bank-of-england-s-miles-says.html
Banks should hold between 17 percent
and 20 percent of capital relative to risk weighted assets as an
“optimum” average  David Miles , a policy maker at the Bank of
 England , said in a speech in Oxford, England today.  “Having too little capital is very costly,” Miles said.
“Having too much loses you a bit.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
